<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="514" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/22:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-01T18:00:00-05:00">April 1, 1930—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>17. National City Bank reports that no progress has been made toward a
                            decision in the matter of the fine of its São Paulo branch. Bank feels
                            that an informal inquiry on your part would help to expedite matters and
                            the Department would be glad to have you make such inquiry unless you
                            perceive some objection thereto. Please report by cable the cause of the
                            delay, action taken by you and result thereof.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
